\overrightarrow r
\frac{1-cost} {t}
\lim_{t\to 0}
\frac {\overrightarrow r(t)} {t}
\lim_{t\to 0} = \frac {\overrightarrow r(t)} {t}=\lim_{t\to 0}(\frac{\sin{t}}{t},\frac{1-\cos{t}}{t^2},1)=(1,\frac{1}{2},1)
\lim_{t\to 0} \frac{\sin{t}}{t}=1
\lim_{t\to 0} \frac{1-\cos{t}}{t^2}
\lim_{t\to 0} \frac{\sin{t}}{2t}=\frac{1}{2}
